Flask and ReactJS Starter

This project contains a simple web application that combines a Flask backend with a ReactJS frontend. 

Follow these instructions to set up and run the application.
    
## Setting up the Flask Backend

cd flask-api
## Install project dependencies 
    pipenv install
## Activate this project's virtualenv
    pipenv shell
## run flask application 
    flask --app src/app.py run 

The Flask server will start running at http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

# Setting up the ReactJS Frontend

cd react-ui

## Install the required Node.js packages:
    npm install
## Start the React development server:
    npm start

The React app will be available at http://localhost:3000/.

## Project Structure
flask-api/ - Contains the Flask backend code.
react-ui/ - Contains the ReactJS frontend code.

## Running the Application
You now have both the Flask backend and ReactJS frontend running. The React app communicates with the Flask backend to provide a seamless web application experience.

